From ada4a6ac7466ee62f1e8d895e8c00abc87382e50 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Jiacheng Yu <yujiacheng3@huawei.com>
Date: Thu, 16 Jul 2026 06:20:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] mm/memory-failure: avoid shmem accounting race during soft
 offline

soft_offline_in_use_page() can invalidate a non-swapcache folio with
mapping_evict_folio().  This path can also remove a shmem folio.

When soft offline races with final inode eviction,
shmem_recalc_inode() can read mapping->nrpages before remove_mapping()
decrements it.  The inode is then left with non-zero i_blocks after
the folio has been removed, potentially leaving the corresponding
shmem block charge unreleased.  It also triggers the final
WARN_ON(inode->i_blocks), which escalates to a panic when
panic_on_warn=1:

    Kernel panic - not syncing: kernel: panic_on_warn set ...
    CPU: 1 UID: 0 PID: 965 Comm: shmem_soft_offl Not tainted 7.2.0-rc4 #1
    Call Trace:
     <TASK>
     dump_stack_lvl+0x39/0xd0
     vpanic+0x653/0x6d0
     panic+0xc2/0xd0
     check_panic_on_warn+0xac/0xb0
     __warn+0xd9/0x210
     __report_bug+0x33e/0x410
     report_bug+0x54/0xf0
     handle_bug+0x258/0x290
     exc_invalid_op+0x13/0x40
     asm_exc_invalid_op+0x16/0x20
    RIP: 0010:shmem_evict_inode+0x58e/0x5f0
     evict+0x239/0x4f0
     iput.part.0+0x34d/0x490
     iput+0x20/0x30
     dentry_unlink_inode+0x173/0x250
     dentry_kill+0x197/0x600
     finish_dput+0x19/0x150
     dput+0x45/0x50
     __fput+0x340/0x6b0
     task_work_run+0x133/0x1b0
     exit_to_user_mode_loop+0x1cd/0x670
     do_syscall_64+0x45c/0x550
     entry_SYSCALL_64_after_hwframe+0x76/0x7e
     </TASK>

This was reproduced by racing MADV_SOFT_OFFLINE with MAP_FIXED
replacement of a shared anonymous shmem mapping.

Commit 0f3c42f522dc ("tmpfs: change final i_blocks BUG to WARNING")
reported a similar race between shmem swapout and inode eviction.
Commit 267a4c76bbdb ("tmpfs: fix shmem_evict_inode() warnings on
i_blocks") fixed that race and another one between fault and truncate.
This is another case where an unsynchronized mapping->nrpages change
escapes shmem's final accounting reconciliation.

Skip generic invalidation for shmem in the soft-offline path and fall
back to migration, avoiding the concurrent mapping->nrpages decrement
from this path.

Fixes: facb6011f399 ("HWPOISON: Add soft page offline support")
Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Signed-off-by: Jiacheng Yu <yujiacheng3@huawei.com>
---
 mm/memory-failure.c | 12 +++++++++---
 1 file changed, 9 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)

diff --git a/mm/memory-failure.c b/mm/memory-failure.c
index 51508a55c405..196e7b841307 100644
--- a/mm/memory-failure.c
+++ b/mm/memory-failure.c
@@ -2782,6 +2782,7 @@ static int soft_offline_in_use_page(struct page *page)
 	long ret = 0;
 	unsigned long pfn = page_to_pfn(page);
 	struct folio *folio = page_folio(page);
+	struct address_space *mapping;
 	char const *msg_page[] = {"page", "hugepage"};
 	bool huge = folio_test_hugetlb(folio);
 	bool isolated;
@@ -2820,12 +2821,17 @@ static int soft_offline_in_use_page(struct page *page)
 		return 0;
 	}
 
-	if (!huge && folio_test_lru(folio) && !folio_test_swapcache(folio))
+	if (!huge && folio_test_lru(folio) && !folio_test_swapcache(folio)) {
 		/*
 		 * Try to invalidate first. This should work for
-		 * non dirty unmapped page cache pages.
+		 * non dirty unmapped page cache folios. Avoid shmem
+		 * here because its accounting reconciliation can race
+		 * with final inode eviction.
 		 */
-		ret = mapping_evict_folio(folio_mapping(folio), folio);
+		mapping = folio_mapping(folio);
+		if (mapping && !shmem_mapping(mapping))
+			ret = mapping_evict_folio(mapping, folio);
+	}
 	folio_unlock(folio);
 
 	if (ret) {
-- 
2.34.1

